libbrahe
------------------------------------------
Brahe is where I put all sorts of useful mathematic functions that don't seem
to fit anywhere else. Among the bits and pieces here, you'll find:

    * A function, brahe_sigdig, that rounds floating-point values to a specific
      number of significant digits -- very useful in scientific and engineering
      applications.
    * Several pseudorandom number generators, including the Marsenne Twister,
      various algorithms by Marsaglia, and ISAAC.
    * Least common multiple and greatest common denominator functions.
    * A few trigonometry functions for finding the inversions of hyperbolic
      sine, cosine, and tangent.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.7-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-9-1
  automake-4-10
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.10.2-1
  gawk-3.1.8-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.coyotegulch.com/products/libbrahe/

Canonical download:
  http://www.coyotegulch.com/distfiles/libbrahe-1.2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libbrahe-1.2.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libbrahe-1.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libbrahe-1.2.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libbrahe-1.2.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libbrahe1.2_2-1.2.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libbrahe-devel-1.2.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libbrahe)
  /usr/bin/brahe_test_fft.exe
  /usr/bin/brahe_test_gcflcm.exe
  /usr/bin/brahe_test_prng.exe
  /usr/bin/brahe_test_rounding.exe
  /usr/bin/brahe_test_trig.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libbrahe.README
  /usr/share/doc/libbrahe/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libbrahe/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libbrahe/NEWS

(libbrahe1.2_2)
  /usr/bin/cygbrahe-1-2-2.dll

(libbrahe-devel)
  /usr/include/libbrahe/mathtools.h
  /usr/include/libbrahe/prng.h
  /usr/lib/libbrahe.a
  /usr/lib/libbrahe.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libbrahe.la

